{"word":"ἐγκαλύπτω","slug":"ἐγκαλύπτω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐγκαλύπτω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>ψω</el>) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to veil in</i> a thing, <i>to wrap up</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>: —<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be veiled</i> or <i>enwrapt</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a> <i>to hide oneself, hide one's face</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; of persons at the point of death, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>; as a mark of shame, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}